12/12/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Top EU officials are supportive of launching of accession talks with Turkey in 2005. European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso will argue Turkey's case at the EU summit later this week, a spokesman said Friday (10 December). Barroso told visiting Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan that the Commission would recommend the start of negotiations early next year. 
Meanwhile, EU Commissioner for Enlargement Olli Rehn said Friday that he believes the EU will decide to start talks with Turkey without new conditions. He added that Turkey has met the political criteria and should receive a date for starting talks. (Reuters - 11/12/04; AP, Anadolu Agency, AFP - 10/12/04)
